  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The clinical safety narrative explicitly requires that the model must demonstrate the pump tip speed remains below 4 m/s across all evaluated operating points to bound shear-induced hemolysis — this tip-speed constraint is a direct patient-safety obligation derived from the device's intended population (paediatric and adult CPB patients at elevated haemolytic risk). All five flow-speed combinations evaluated include operating points approaching this 4 m/s threshold, and the relative hemolysis index acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate) is conditioned on that tip-speed bound being satisfied.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
